  "texts": [
    "During training, Q θ (s t, a t) and π φ (a t | s t) are optimised with stochastic gradients ∇ θ J Q (θ) and ∇ φ J π (φ) designed corresponding to soft policy evaluation and soft policy improvement, respectively (see ( 6) and (10) in Haarnoja et al. 2018b).",
    "With these gradients, SAC updates the critic and actor networks byθ ← θ -λ Q ∇ θ J Q (θ), (2.12) φ ← φ -λ π ∇ φ J π (φ), (2.13)where λ Q and λ π are the learning rates of Q-function and policy, respectively.",
    "Typically, two Q-functions are trained independently, then the minimum of the Q-functions is brought into the calculation of stochastic gradient and policy gradient.",
    "This method is also used in our work to increase the stability and speed of training.",
    "Also, SAC supports automatic adjustment of temperature α by optimisation:α * = arg min α E a t ∼π * [-α log π * (a t | s t; α) -α H]."
  ],
